$ Oracle: backup
@ backup

{ Logical and physical backups

  table { ll
    → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/backup/logical[Logical] ☰ → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/backup/physical[Physical]

     Tables, stored procedures etc. ☰ Copies of → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/data[database files]
     Extracted with → development/databases/Oracle/tools/Data-Pump ☰ → development/databases/Oracle/tools/RMAN or operating system utilities
     Slower but finer granularity ☰ Fast but larger granularity
     Complete transportability ☰ Limited transportability

  table }

}
{ Protected database

  Databases whose backups are managed by *Recovery Appliance* are called *protected databases*.

}
{ Binary compression

  ? The size of backups is reduced with *binary compression* (see → development/databases/Oracle/tools/RMAN)

}


sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery

  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/backup/archival
